      "purposeInStoryline": "This is the opening lesson of the unit. It launches the anchoring phenomenon — fertiliser granules clumping, washing soda crystals developing a white crust, and table salt remaining unchanged — and asks learners to confront the puzzle: all three are salts, so why do they behave so differently? By the end of this lesson learners have built a shared definition of 'salt', sorted physical samples into classification categories, constructed an initial class model, and posted their first wondering questions on the DQB. Every subsequent lesson will return to this phenomenon and this board.",
